,Recommended,313080,16236166,"Posted: 6 June, 2015",all,Rinnsanity,"Imagine taking GTA5, Payday 2, Battlefield: Hardline, Doorkickers, and Frozen Synapse, and throw them into a bowl and mix them all together, then put them in the oven at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes.The result would be some nasty stuff nobody would ever want, but at least it would give you good reason to not bake ever again and play The Masterplan instead.I've watched and played this game since they jumped into Early Access last year and enjoyed every minute of it. I suppose that micro-managing a robbery/heist wouldn't sound too exciting, but the very first time you walk out with that cash in hand (and no cops giving you a hard time), it gets you hooked.There are many different ways to complete each heist, but eventually it all boils down to busting through the front door with SMG's, Shotguns, and Rifles, and mowing down everyone, greatly hoping that you make it out with at least half the loot. OR, you could go the stealthy methodical route with silenced pistols and tranquilizer guns, taking down cameras and stuffing people into rooms. Each heist has their own way of making you think, with their own way of rewarding you by doing things by the book. Some heists you absolutely have to go in armed to the teeth, and some will brutally punish you for not sneaking your way in.The Soundtrack is simple and somewhat dynamic, but still does its job good. Makes the setting feel like a real 70's action flick. Sadly, neither Austin Powers nor Foxxy Cleopatra make a cameo in-game.5/5 Stars11/10 Would heist a kiosk again$50 out of $100,000 loot taken, with a 75% evidence cleaning fee."
