76561198016277251,Not Recommended,313080,20117922,"Posted: 30 December, 2015",all,AlexMBrennan,"Interesting concept, but badly executed; only buy if you have a high tolerance for frustration:1) controls are frequently inadequate; e.g. if you order someone to close a door they will frequently fail because they are standing in a spot that blocks the door, so be prepared to micromanage and restart a few times until you get the hang of it. This is not a matter of skill but abysmal pathfinding (e.g. on some maps, the first time you click will send characters walking all over the map instead of going through an open door) and animation (when you order a goon to lock a door there is a 70% chance that he'll get stuck in a loop, shuffling trying to get close enough to the door)2) game mechanics are odd, and terribly explained - e.g. the tutorial teaches the player that you can hold people at gunpoint to control them, but fails to mention that this only works in the tutorial (after that, it takes at least TWO guns to control people; keep in mind that you only get a single gun at the start until you grind enough cash to buy more). Have fun figuring that out.3) game is unstable - in my experience, there is a 50% chance the game will crash when you finish a missionEdit to add: And now the game crashes every time I try to launch it. Too bad, I guess"
