76561198139144247,Recommended,313080,22121955,"Posted: 29 March, 2016",all,sir groovyjoel14,this is a message to the developer due to the fact i have talked with the door kickers developer and i was wondering if you could make a map edditor loke door kickers
,Recommended,313080,16916522,"Posted: 6 July, 2015",all,COCAINE DINOSAUR,"For those that don't know, or are interested in buying;The Masterplan is a top down strategypuzzlegame. From appearance, it looks like a Payday: The Heist gone Door Kickers(but being the criminals) mixed with a crime-like aspect of Hotline Miami... with polished gameplay with many awesome features and unique and appealing graphics. There is a lot to this game and I'm going to try and cover most of it.When I first bought this game, I was dissapointed. The first mission is quite confusing to someone who has never seen gameplay or a video of how it's done and the game's version of a 'tutorial' is confusing and quite unhelpful. This, being a con. However because of easy controls and UI you will figure it out within a minute or so. After you complete missions you go back to your hideout, which, is mostly pointless other than for you to mail order yourself weapons and accessories, or to hire another goon (Hitman/robber/whatever you want to call it). The more goons the better. Once onto levels with security you will want to hire another goon and make sure two of your three goons have guns. It takes two guns pointed at guard(s) to make their resistance level stay at 0 (Full circle), while your third goon beats them up. The gameplay is quite fluid and there is no pause button, but there is slow motion which is essentially the same thing except that the game is still moving. (reaaaaally slowww)Due to the top down, slow paced aspect the game can probably run on any PC or laptop. The graphics aren't really changeable (Not like you would want/need to). And the game rarely crashes and doesn't ever crash on startup (for me, and I haven't seen any crash on startup reports on the forums). The developers and moderators on the forums, to those interested in the community, are very very nice. They seem to be open to critisism and are nice to the players and those asking questions on the forums. They reply to nearly every post, crash log, bug report, suggestion, etc etc.Lets talk about how the game does in its genres.Strategy 9/10. Very strategical, will have you dieing/running to your car from cops/shooting cops, picking places to hold people up, hide bodies, etc. Needs some working on the paths your goons follow but that is it.Action 5/10. Not in 5 as bad but 5 as in it depends how you play. If you are the other 50% you will refrain from any 'action' and only hold people up and knock them out. If you are the other 50% you will be seeing lots of action, like shooting at cops, security, civilians, running to your car before the police show up, etc. So it heavily depends on how you choose to play.Puzzle 4/10. Most people are probably suprised when I classified this as a Puzzle game, however, most players would agree. It's not really a puzzle game, it just has puzzle aspects of it. The whole mission is essentially a puzzle that you have to figure out how to get through a room and get the pieces inside of it using means of holding people up, telling hostages what to do, hiding bodies, locking doors and lots more. Since the game only has puzzle aspects, and isn't a puzzle game. So if you aren't into puzzle games, but this title has caught your eye, keep looking. If you are looking for puzzle games, this isn't one.Now, to other qualities of the game..Graphics 10/10. It has its own unique, and good looking style of graphics. Whereas, if you are looking for an HD clean realistic looking graphics, you won't find it here.Bugs/Glitches 7/10. The game has bugs/glitches but they are few and far between. Most that get reported get patched that same day/week.Gameplay 10/10. Challenging as hell, exciting, keeps you on the edge of your chair hoping you don't slip up and ruin your heist.This game is unique, fun, challenging, appealing, and very exciting. If nothing I covered in this interests you, check out more reviews, gameplays, to get a feel of the game. If you still aren't interested, I suggest you look for a different game.OVERALL:9/10"
