,Not Recommended,313080,13201252,"Posted: 2 December, 2014",all,tajmone,"GOOD POTENTIAL, BUT TOO BUGGY FOR NOW! The game is quite nice, and it's developing around a good idea. Hopefully it will end up in a good final product. As for now, the main issue is constant crashes. In the last week there have been 2 consecutive updated (5.0 and 5.1) but for some (like me) it just meant that the game became unplayable because it crashes every time I choose to play a heist.Unfortunately, because Steam App handles all the updates automatically, I'll have to wait for the next update hoping (let's cross fingers) that it will work again. And updates are not all that often.So, if you are looking for a game to play, I advice you wait till the game is less buggy. If you are ok with bugs and just want to support the project, then give it a try.Regarding the game-play experience I have mixed feelings: I really like the game and the ""idea"" of how to conduct it; but I find that game controls are a bit clumbsy. Even though I've spent a good amount of hours playing it, I often end up stumbling while I try to put into action game strategies due to the difficoulties of having to control the characters with mouse and keyboard -- too many passages (clicks, menus, queued actions, ecc). At times I've found that frustration is more than fun during gameplay. Hopefully, this might change with future editions of The Masterplan, but it would require some rethinking of the user-interface/controls-implementation on the developers' side.Overall, it's a very original game and I really hope it will develop into a great final product. But I don't feel like advising to buy it at this stage -- at your own risk: you might be amongst the unlucky ones who end up always crashing!"
