,Not Recommended,313080,18089787,"Posted: 18 September, 2015",all,Blandman Bob,"Review update:Game is abandoned. Shark Punch, the creators behind this game, handed over the rights to some other company, which presumably from the fact their website doesn't work anymore, had shut down shortly after.The game was fairly decent, but the crashes were, and are still a problem.If the damn developers actually cared to have at least worked on this to make it a little more stable, it probably would've worked out to be a decent choice to buy.Trust me though, crashing at Fort Knox, towards the very, very end, was an absolute buzzkill.In a 'out of ten' rating system, I give this game a five. I would like to point out, while making the statement in regards to the Fort Knox deal, that the rating change is not out of experience bias revolving around that statement, and the rating is in fact going towards the overall events surrounding the game, and what has happened.Stay away from this game. If it were possible to do a personal review with the Valve team, to discuss the matters behind this, so that I may or may not be eligable for a refund, rather than base it on a flawed steam time system, I would so definitely take that, to get my money back.The game had good potential. But the workshop community is a ♥♥♥♥ing joke, and so are the morons who couldn't even maintain this game.If the game somehow becomes free temporarily in the future, feel free to give it a go, but if I were you dear reader, I would just stay far, far away.Original review (September 15th, 2015. Ihadrecommended it.):It's a pretty decent game. I like it a lot.The only issues I have with this game is THE FREAKING CRASHES! Seriously. It crashes a lot. Well, not a lot per se, but it crashes at the most unfortunate times. (Unrelated Note: Removing the Crash Dumper folder in the game's files delays these Crashes, but they still can happen at any possible time.)The other issue being that there is no save feature. Sure, it autosaves, but without a manual save option, you can't save on important setups and maps just for safety from these annoying crashes.All in all, this game still has bugs and issues, and it was sent out of Early Access a bit too Early.I recommend this, but I also recommend caution, and not playing it for a extensively long time, or else you'll be in tears.8.8/10Would Crash on (Spoilers?) Warehouse 9 Diamond Room again."
